  = must: compute finite prime-power contributions without expanding beyond requested bounds
  = must: keep k = 1 prime contributions visible as theta layer
  = must: keep k >= 2 higher-prime-power contributions visible as the psi-theta difference
  = must: report interval movement by exponent layer and by prime-power event when requested
  = must: compare layer sums to psi(x), theta(x), and psi(x)-theta(x)
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_prime_power_decomposition_not_rh_evidence
  = must: keep special-prime families subordinate until this whole-field object is understood
  - never: claim finite prime-power decomposition proves RH, disproof, or zero behavior
  - never: treat a large layer contribution as causal proof of explicit-formula error

